inn1.comm: Johnson starts by going down leg and Shehzad cashes in by glancing the length ball off his pads for four to the fine leg area
will that go for four as well? Full and straight, Shehzad drives that, rather pushes that with good timing, down the ground between mid on and mid off. But the outfield is slow and they get only two
length delivery outside off and angling away, left alone
on length again and outside off, pushed by Shehzad towards cover with a forward lean
bangs in a back of length ball outside off, Shehzad stays back and defends
ends the over they way he started it - down the leg side and that's tucked to fine leg off the pad for one
takes a step across and flicks the offcutter from length outside off to fine leg, he did connect but it was a risky shot
on length outside off, pushed to cover
wider outside off, he stays back and goes across a bit to cut to third man
drives and misses! Richardson makes him drive with a length ball well outside off, Sarfraz chased with a forward lean and missed
touch shorter and coming in from outside off, takes a step across and defends

there's a mix up, chance for a run out! Sarfraz taps the ball to point and wants a single, Shehzad doesn't so Sarfraz has to come back. Maxwell had to dive to his right and then throw, he missed the direct hit, or it might have been a run out
edged, but it bounces once before reaching the slip fielder. Johnson had pitched it on length outside off and it was angling away as Shehzad want back to defend
short ball outside off, another edge, this thick one goes to third man for one
another shot off the back foot, a thickish edge goes to third man again
fuller and a bit wider, he drives but Bailey at cover point dives to his left to save a few runs
cracking shot! It was pitched up again, there was room too and Shehzad pounced on it with a forward lean and crashed it past point with a drive
bang on target, on length on off stump and he defends it back
brings it in from back of length outside off, Sarfraz pushes on the off side
length delivery well outside off and shaping away further, that's a wide
still stays wide outside off but this one swings in a bit and it's not wide
back of length outside off, takes a step across and tucks it to third man

length ball outside off, Shehzad defends it to cover. Warner at cover saw Shehzad was outside his crease and launched a flat and quick throw for the stumps which nearly hit Shehzad, who had to jump to his right to avoid the ball
closer to the off stump on length, Shehzad defends it back now
fuller outside off and he drives it to point
on length outside off, it's tapped to point and Maxwell from point gets a direct hit at the non-striker's end even though there was nobody backing up
short ball outside off with the angle, he lets it go
quicker delivery on length outside off with the scrambled seam, he drives and missed. Was beaten by pace
touch fuller close to off, he pushes it to mid-off gently and runs for a single immediately, it might be close but he makes it
bouncer for Shehzad, quick delivery again! That was a nasty delivery as Shehzad managed to duck under it
on length this time outside off, pushed to Bailey at cover and that's only one from the over
another chance, not quite! The back of length ball was tapped to point and they set off for a run but came back in time as Maxwell threw it
goes fuller now with a scrambled seam and Sarfraz drives it from outside off past cover point for two in the gap
goes short and down the leg side for a wide

in the air but wide of midwicket, but is he run out?? The delivery came in from outside off and it lobbed in the air wide of midwicket, they were coming back for the second the throw was over Haddin's head and he caught it with one hand and threw to the stumps but Sarfraz dived to make it in time
another run out chance? What is Pakistan doing? Pushed to cover for a quick single, Bailey dives to his right and misses the direct hit at the bowler's. Had he hit, Sarfraz was gone for sure!
length ball outside off, driven straight to cover so no chance for a single
starts with a full toss on leg and it's swept to fine leg. They were looking for a second, mind you, but they settled for one
tossed up and full toss on leg again, swept to short fine leg for a quick single
full delivery towards middle and leg, driven down to mid off
length ball on leg stump, defends it to midwicket with a forward lean
full and outside leg, swept to fine leg for one
slower through the air on off an turning away, thick edge goes to the off side
loud appeal for lbw first ball! Sarfraz took a step down and moved across, tried to flick and was hit low in front of the off stump. But it looked like it was missing off stump
length ball on the off stump, he defends it back
angles it in form outside off, turned to deep midwicket for easy two
slower one at 113kph outside off, on length and it comes in, Sarfraz chases and misses
back of length from outside off, he moves across a bit and glances it fine down the leg side in the gap with the angle for four
fullish outside off, pushed through extra cover towards long-off
on length outside off, pushed past cover for one
with a bit of flight outside off, leans forward and blocks
charges down the track and drives the length ball on middle and off inside out over the cover for a beautiful four
lbw appeal as he's struck in front of leg while trying to sweep but it was gong down leg
quick single after it was pushed to mid-on, excellent running because they called for it early
length delivery towards middle and off, he defends it back
touch wider outside off, he cuts it off the back foot to third man
full on the pads outside leg, flicked past square leg for one
comes down the wicket to loft it on the leg side, he doesn't middle but gets enough to clear mid-on for two
charges down again, pushes to cover point and Sarfraz was well out of his crease. Finch leaps to grab it with his left hand and tries a direct hit, but misses
turning in from outside off on length, pushed to the leg side
flight and outside off, makes him drive to cover with a forward lean
comes down and nearly gets yorked to defend it back
flight and turn from outside off, Sarfraz closes the face of the bat to the leg side
shorter and flatter with turn, pushed down the ground to long-on
flight outside off, Shehzad comes down and chips it down to long-on for one more
well outside off on length, guides it to third man easily
outside off again with the angle, he cuts it late behind square to third man for two more
slower one from the back of the hand outside off, cut late again to third man area
angled in sharply towards middle stump, it's full and Sarfraz defends it back
tries the yorker, but it's full on the pads and he flicks it to deep midwicket
slower one again from the back of the hand, pitched well outside off but came in after pitching and failed to connect, managed only an inside edge
leans forward and defends it back
short of length well outside off, sharp turn and it's cut off the back foot to cover point
he goes back for the short of length ball and tucks it to fine leg after the turn
comes down the track to push but the ball goes to slip after an inside edge and hitting the pad
well outside off on length, goes back and makes room to cut to point
nearly carries to square leg! He moved across a bit and swept it firmly from length, it almost carried to the fielder
on length on off, he blocks it back
goes back as the ball angles in towards moiddle and leg, cut to backward point
comes down and pushes it to long-off by taking it on the full
flighted on off stump, Sarfraz unleashes his favourite sweep shot and finds the gap between deep midwicket and fine leg for four
slightly full on middle and leg, defends it back to the bowler
on length on leg and going down further, Sarfraz is hit on the pad
tossed up around off, pushed to midwicket
touch shorter outside off, Shehzad rocks back and punches it between cover point and point in the gap for two
fullish around off, he comes down and drives it towards the non-striker. Lyon dives and gets a hand
stays in the crease to defends the length ball
goes down on a knee and sweeps the ball from middle and leg to fine leg. It was in the air for a bit
on length outside off, Sarfraz charges down and lofts it powerfully to the cow corner for four by taking it on the full
flighted and full on middle, driven inside out to cover
flighted on leg this time, another close chance as it was pushed to midwicket but they decided against the single
touch quicker on the off stump, he blocks it back
on middle on length, he goes back and cuts it to the off side
comes down and takes it on the full to drive it back, the ball sneaks through Doherty's legs
uses his feet again and smashes the ball in the air to the long-on area. He's hit it straight enough to beat the fielder as it raced to the boundary
takes a step down and drives the full delivery from outside off to sweeper cover
fullish outside off, easily driven to deep point for one more
back of length outside off, taps it between point and cover point and they decide against the single
back of length from outside off with the angle, turned to deep midwicket for one
bangs it in short around middle, Sarfraz goes on his toes to defend it back
bangs in another one outside off, and Sarfraz was looking to slap-sweep that but he missed completely
tossed up on off, some turn too, the batsman pushes it to cover
drifts down the leg side, the batsman goes down to play a paddle fine for a single
uses his feet and pushes the tossed up delivery down to long off
waits in the crease, but this is quicker from the bowler, Sarfraz can only defend it to off
stretches forward to push the tossed up delivery to off, but finds cover point
whackolicious! He clears his front leg and slaps it over midwicket. Not sure he needs a drink, but the carts roll in anyway
this is past the first slip, off the edge, but that was a rank poor delivery.. A low full toss and deserved to be punished
another edge past the lone slip fielder, but this one is cut off by the third man.. No feet movement there from Shehzad.. He will keep that slip fielder interested with those shots
calll for a quick single to mid-off and they complete it with ease. It was a fuller one on the stumps and Sarfraz just takes the pace off it, pushing it softly down the pitch
he waits on the back foot and defends the back of length delivery to off
looks to drive at this fuller delivery but gets another outside edge.. this one is much squarer though and he takes a couple by the time third man runs to his right
solid defence against a short of length thunderbolt, he drops it down towards the off side
back of length around off stump, the batsman guides it down to third man
shuffles across and punches this length delivery to deep cover, plays it stylishly on the up
gets cramped for room as this short one follows him, but does pretty well in the end clipping it away to deep square leg, goes past his previous ODI best
waits in the crease and steers the length delivery to third man
angled in from wide of crease, the batsman pushes it straight to short cover
looks for a single down to third man with a dab, but the fielder at point keeps the batsmen on their ends
pushes this wider outside off, not the line to bowl when you have no one covering in the deep.. Shehzad stands tall and punches it through the gap to bring up his half-century. Easily done
steps out of the crease, but pads this one away to off after realising it is turning in
goes across the stumps and tucks it to square leg
tossed up wider outside off, draws the batsman into a drive, but Shehzad can only push it back down the pitch
plays it with the turn to the leg side but cannot beat square leg
moves to the leg side but is cramped for room as it turns in, and bounces a touch extra, pushed to cover point
sees the length is marginally short and swings his bat across the line, doesn't get it off the middle but picks up a single to deep square leg
dropped at mid-off by none other than Bailey!! He drops catches, really? That has been hit straight to him, low to his left.. an easy chance for someone of his calibre.
he is playing a bit loose here.. pulls it in the air through midwicket.. picks up a single to the deep
short delivery, but this is way over the batsman
now Sarfraz gets to his half-century - his first in ODIs - with a cut past backward point. He raises his arms, takes his helmet off.. This is a huge celebration, shows what it means to him.
he stays in the crease and slices the length delivery straight to Warner at point
this time he is able to chop it past Warner, for a couple to deep backward point
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman shuffles across and tucks it straight to square leg

the finger goes up! It looks a bit tricky to the naked eye. Shehzad was looking to play a premeditated sweep but this was fuller than what he expected, and a touch quicker too.. Shehzad misses but this looks like it's angling away from the off.. Lyon is bowling round the wicket by the way.. this doesn't seem to have turned at all. The decision is reviewed.. and rightly so because this was way way outside off..
slower this time, the batsman comes forward and shows off his forward defence
that is smartly played! He comes down the pitch and makes room too, slaps it over the umpire's head for a couple.. Had he timed it better, that was headed for the boundary
looks to hit it across the line, but still doesn't get the timing, picks up a single to long on
top edge, but it lands safely at deep backward square leg.. Sarfraz looks for the big sweep but was not in control there
tossed up on off, Sarfraz pushes it straight to cover
superb timing! Sarfraz uses his feet and just chips it over midwicket, that has raced to the boundary
waits an extra second and chops this flatter one to the right of short third man for a quick single
another quick single! the batsman pushes it between the two fielders at cover and calls early
tossed up, the batsman leans forward and eases it to long on
this is dabbed to the leg side, behind square for yet another easy single
slower from Lyon, the batsman is a bit outfoxed by the pace, can only defend it to off in the end
some turn in form outside off but Shehzad waits for the spin, then punches it through cover for a single to deep
another smart chip over midwicket! He is not trying to belt it to Abu Dhabi, just gets close to the pitch of the delivery and punches it over the infield
allows the ball to turn and nudges it to the right of midwicket for a single
walks way across the stumps and nudges it almost from the middle stump line to pick up a couple fine on the leg side
uses his feet to get close to the pitch of the delivery, then punches it down to long on
he has pulled it straight to midwicket! It's a flatter one on a length, not really short enough and the batsman is not able to keep it down
tossed up delivery on the stumps, the batsman pushes it back to the bowler
flatter and quicker on stumps, the batsman defends it off the back foot
comes down the pitch and drives the tossed up delivery to long off
draws the batsman into a loose drive with a loopy one, it grips the surface and takes the outside edge, but there is no one at slip for Sarfraz
quicker on the stumps, the batsman pushes it softly to cover for a quick single
here goes another! Fuller and wider outside off, and all Sarfraz can do it slice it straight to point.. Another set batsman falls to a harmless delivery
fires in a yorker outside off, Misbah digs it out to the off side.. Mitchell Johnson immediately looks back - he had dropped his towel in the run up
sharp bouncer to welcome the captain! That doesn't get up too much but Misbah just ducks under it
another short one, Misbah ducks again, but this is slightly to the leg side

big hesitation! Misbah slices it past backward point.. comes down the pitch for a single, then sees his partner is not coming down, he turns back.. by the time Asad is already charging down.. Luckily Misbah turns back in time to complete the run
stays on the back foot and defends the back of length delivery to off
short one to test Asad but the batsman is not backing off, he is quick to swivel and pull it over midwicket for his first boundary
he almost lobs it to cover! That is smartly bowled.. tossed up, spins away, draws batsman into a loose drive.. it just lands short of Maxwell
he comes forward and defends the loopy delivery to the off side
flatter, and it turns away after pitching, Misbah defends it off the back foot
bowls the arm ball now, it keeps coming in. Misbah is equal to the task, defends it solidly off the front foot
tossed up delivery outside off, Misbah defends it to backward point
flatter and quicker on off, Misbah keeps strike with a punch to deep cover
bowls it full on the off, easily driven down to long on for a single
plays a premeditated paddle but can only play it as far as short fine leg for a quick single
flatter and quicker on off, Misbah goes deep in the crease and defends
he goes down early and paddles it from outside off to fine leg
he looks for the big hit down the ground but doesn't get hold of it! Toe-ends it to long on
tossed up on off, Misbah flicks it to deep square leg for a single. He keeps the strike
slower and loopy outside off, turns away too, Misbah pushes it to backward point
no turn this time, it keeps coming in, Misbah defends it down the pitch
flatter outside off, although it turns away but the length means Misbah has time to crunch it to deep cover
looks for a single to deep cover but cannot beat Maxwell in the infield
he comes forward and drives the tossed up delivery to long off
fuller, but drifting on the pads, the batsman tickles it to backward square leg for a single. keeps the strike again
he goes down on his knee early and paddles it from around off stump, picks up a single down the leg side
flatter and quicker on the stumps, Asad goes deep in his crease and pushes it past cover
now the reverse paddle! But this one is pushed quicker and wider outside off, Misbah doesn't connect
he repeats the shot and gets it off the middle this time, slides it past the short third man fielder
this is full and wide, way outside off, Misbah is still hell bent on a paddle shot, gets an under edge and it rolls past the leg stump.. that was very very close
he nudges it to the leg side, but straight to square leg
flighted on the middle stump, Asad defends it down the pitch
much slower this time, Asad gets time to get back and push it through cover point for a single
tossed up on off stump, Misbah pushes forward and defends to off
pushed a touch quicker on the leg stump line, the batsman eases it to long on
loopy delivery on off, Asad goes for a slog sweep by getting his front leg out of the way, but gets a big bottom edge as he plays it towards square leg
quicker delivery on the stumps, the batsman defends it down the pitch
tossed up delivery, Asad uses his feet and drives it past wide mid on
another paddle sweep from Misbah! He takes it from wide outside off and takes a single down to fine leg
flatter delivery, playing with the turn the batsman tucks it straight to backward square leg
he takes his eyes off as he goes for the paddle, this is just over Haddin's shoulder.. A half-hearted appeal for lbw.. it's given a leg bye but it was off the bat
he stays back and defends the flatter delivery down the pitch
drifting on to the pads, Misbah nudges it straight to backward square leg
flatter on the stumps, the batsman chops it in the gap at cover for a quick one
he goes for a sweep, takes it from in front of the middle stump and plays it fine.. Gets a glove on that actually.. Had he missed, he was a gonner
tossed up on the stumps, pushed to cover

one tight single too many! Maxwell does the job. That was pushed towards cover where Maxwell dives to his left, but doesn't collect it cleanly. The batsmen think they can run off the misfield, but the ball is only an arms length away from the fielder.. Maxwell gets there in no time and fires it at the striker's end where Misbah is comfortably short, despite a superman-like dive
on length outside off and that's pushed down to long-off to get off the mark straightaway
flighted on middle and leg, gentle push towards midwicket for a quick single
flighted outside off, takes a step down and drives it to long-on
turning it in from outside off from length, Akmal leans forward and blocks
touch shorter on leg stump, tucked with the turn to fine leg
bit more flight on middle stump, helps it to midwicket off the back foot
fuller on middle stump and Shafiq paddle-sweeps it fine down leg for one
touch flatter and quicker on off stump, nudged wide of midwicket for one more
length delivery coming in, thick inside edge rolls down towards mid-on
coming in from back of length now, Akmal defends it back
back of length again towards middle and leg, helped to deep midwicket for a single
bangs it in shorter outside off, Shafiq stays back on his toes and defends it towards point
well outside off, swished off the back foot to sweeper cover
fuller towards middle and leg, turned to deep midwicket with the angle

he strikes first ball in the new spell, with a soft dismissal! It was a simple and full delivery on off and Akmal simply chipped it straight to mid-off to be pouched by Smith. Time to finish the grapes in the pavilion
full delivery swinging in towards leg stump, Alam gets a leg bye to fine leg
beaten! Length delivery outside off with the angle, Shafiq pushes without footwork and misses
goes down the leg side for a wide with a length delivery
back of length on middle and leg, turned towards short fine leg for one
offcutter on length outside off, he rolled his fingers over that one, Fawad tapped it to point
makes room initially but the ball is on target on the off stump, so he has to defend it back
brings it in from back of length towards the batsman who defends it to midwicket
full on off now, driven back firmly but Kane Richardson gets a hand to it
short on off stump and pulled to deep midwicket for one
length delivery outside off with the angle, tapped to third man for another
he makes room but Richardson pitches (nearly) a yorker, Shafiq digs it out back to the bowler who throws it back again and hits the stumps. Lots of back and forths there
crackalicious! It was full and in the zone for Shafiq, he stayed in his position and smacked it over the wide long-on boundary for a massive six
bit of flight outside off, Fawad stayed back to defend and the extra bounce got a bit of glove to go to slip after a bounce
pitched outside off and he tries to sweep by going far too across but can't connect it
length delivery outside off, pushed to cover this time for one
charges down the track, mid-off is in, and he clears the infield easily with a lofted shot by taking it on the full and gets a four despite a slow outfield
on leg this time on length, tucked to short fine leg for one
pitches on leg and goes down the leg side for a wide after the turn
can't clear the field this time, gives an easy catch to mid-off! He charged down the track again to clear mid-off but gave an easy catch to Johnson at the edge of the circle
swings in towards the pads and hits them as Fawad can't connect
rolled his fingers over this one but it was at 142kph on length outside off, pushed down to mid-on
back of length and angled in, tucked to fine leg for one off the back foot
back of length around off and he rolled his fingers a bit, Afridi poked and missed outside off
short ball on the leg side, Afridi ducks under it
fullish on leg stump, pushes it down to mid-on
angled is in towards off stump, Fawad has no room to put it away and defends it on the off side
fuller towards middle and leg, flicked a bit awkwardly to midwicket at the last moment
fullish on the off stump and it's pushed down to mid-off
back of length outside off, Fawad taps it to point
angled in from off stump, Fawad tried to make room but didn't get any and it was pushed to cover
towards middle stump from length, Fawad takes a quick single by tapping it on the off side and he keeps strike
short on middle and that's pulled to deep midwicket
full and outside off, Afridi goes for a wild swing and misses
back of length on the off stump, tapped wide of point towards third man for one and he's off the mark
on the off stump and Fawad defends it on the off side
short ball, pulled and oh that's hit the square leg umpire on the right ankle. Fawad hit it well wide of both midwicket and short midwicket but couldn't get it beyond the umpire
length ball outside off, pushed down gently to mid-off
full on middle and leg and Fawad makes room to smash it back along the ground to beat mid-on and collect his first boundary
slower legcutter from the back of the hand outside off, defends it to point
another slower on from back of the hand, this one on off stump and Fawad defends it back
on length outside off, pushed wide of cover for one
on length outside off, swept like Sarfraz to square leg for one
on length just outside off, driven wide of cover for one and he keeps strike
back of length and cutting in from just outside off, Fawad makes room for a wild slog on the leg side but misses it completely
nearly in the block hole, it's flicked off the pads down to fine leg where Warner appears like Flash to keep it to one
angled across on length outside off, Afridi tries a big swing and misses too
sways down the leg side with a short ball for a wide

wild swing, he connects with an edge and it's taken on second attempt at slip! It was another big swing outside off, Afridi got a thick edge and the ball was going over Smith's head. He leapt and got both hands to it, but it popped out and went to his left, Haddin wanted to get it too but Smith got it in the end with a dive
length delivery on the stumps, pushed to the leg side
on length outside off, tapped off the back foot to third man
length delivery on middle and leg, he leans forward and defends
turn from outside off, Wahab looked to sweep and the ball lobbed up after an edge and off the pad towards silly point, Haddin leapt but couldn't get there
on length outside off, pushed to cover this time
leans forward and tucks the ball towards square leg for one
flighted on middle, swept fine to fine leg for one
flighted outside off and that's pushed back to the bowler
fullish delivery outside off, pushed to cover
full on middle and leg, pushed delicately to cover for a quick single as Bailey tried for a direct hit at the keeper's end but could not. If he had, Wahab was gone
missed it completely! It was a full delivery angled in towards middle and leg, Wahab looked to flick it with no timing and was bowled
full and down the leg side for a wide
fullish towards middle and leg again, thick inside edge goes to square leg

is he run out on debut for a duck? Indeed! He tucked the length ball to midwicket for a single that didn't exist. He was sent back by Fawad and Smith was too quick to throw the ball to Haddin who whips the bails off
on length outside off, pushed softly past cover in the gap and they come back for the second in time
slower delivery from the back of the hand on leg stump, he makes some room to drive it to cover
another one from the back of the hand, this one short of length and it's cut to point, still no run
angled in now towards the batsman, tucked to deep midwicket for one
full delivery outside off, driven to cover
angled in towards the leg stump, he makes room but can't clear midwicket
full on the off stump, he defends and the ball whizzes back to the bowler
full on the off stump, he slogs and can't clear midwicket
full outside off this time, he swishes and hits it in the air to third man
stifled appeal as it goes fine down the leg side and the fielder cuts it off in the boundary but the umpire says he got bat on that
back of length outside off, defends the ball to cover point
lofted over mid-off with rather ease. It was full outside off and he chipped it high in the air to clear the infield for two
attempted yorker is a low full toss on middle and leg and it's pushed to cover
back of length outside off, slaps it down the ground to long-off, but only for one
on length and angled in, driven towards cover
legcutter from the back of the hand comes in from outside off and surprises Babar as he tries to defend

something has happened in the match, it's a wicket! From back of the hand again outside off, Babar waited for it to smash it on off but managed a top edge and it was taken easily by Maxwell near point
he makes room for the ball cutting in, and guess what - he can't clear point
bit fuller now and it's turned away to deep square leg and he keeps strike
in the block hole outside off, Fawad looks to tap it on off but misses
yorker on middle stump now, digs it out to midwicket for one

Irfan has been beaten twice and he's run out! The slow leg cutter beat him after pitching outside off first as he tried to poke, Fawad wanted the strike but Irfan realised it too late. Haddin passed on the ball to Richardson who was near the middle of the pitch and took a couple of steps before knocking over the stumps as if Irfan was on another planet

inn2.comm: flights it on leg and turns it down leg for a wide
sharp turn now from middle on length and beating Warner
another wide down leg as Warner looks to sweep it with the turn
touch shorter and Warner goes back to pull it to deep midwicket
flighted well outside off and Finch waits for it and then swishes it to the deep backward point area for four on his first ball
comes forward and defends the length ball back to the bowler
rocks back, makes room and cuts it fiercely but straight to Shehzad at cover point

edged, but did that carry! Beautiful delivery from Hasan - flighted well outside off, Finch pressed forward to defend and the ball turned from length to take the edge to go to slip. Replays suggest the ball did not carry, it has bounced in front of Umar Akmal at slip even though he was celebrating
length delivery just outside off, Warner stays back to defend it
stifled appeal for lbw, back of length towards middle stump, Warner stayed back and got an inside edge onto the pads on the leg stump
back of length on the off stump, Warner stays in the crease to defend it back
back of length towards the pads, helped to fine leg off the back foot for one
beats him outside off! It was angled across from length, Finch prodded forward to push it on off but missed it
connects this time, it was on length again but Finch drove it past mid-off in the gap for two even as Wahab dived but couldn't keep it to one
flighted around middle, sharp turn but Warner gets into position to sweep it to the fine leg boundary for four
much better from Hasan - on length and well outside off, Warner goes back to defend
makes Warner go back again without giving him room as he pushes it to midwicket
goes back to work it to square leg
put down, but it was a great effort! Warner swept it to backward square leg, Fawad leapt in the air and got his left hand to it but it popped out or it would have been a stunner
goes back to defend the length ball from outside off
he gets some extra bounce with the back of length ball outside off, Finch makes use of it by cutting it over point for four
on length just outside off, pushed down to mid-off by Finch
touch shorter with the angle outside off, Finch hops back to defend to cover
swing and a miss! It was fullish just outside off, Finch drove it down the ground but the movement after the ball pitched beat him
wider outside off, it wasn't a bad ball but he got on top of the bounce and punched it past point on the off side for a four

beaten again, has he edged it! Misbah is reviewing it. It was outside off, Finch stayed back to defend it, the ball angled across after pitching on middle and the Pakistan players seem confident of an edge. It didn't look like there was enough evidence to overturn the decision, but there was a noise for sure when the ball passed the bat. Not 100% proof, but maybe enough for the third umpire
pitched up and Warner smacks it to the long-on boundary with a slog sweep down on one knee for four
goes back and tucks it to backward square leg for one
on length outside off, Smith leans forward and defends
takes a step down and defends it to point from length
he makes him drive but it was too full and Smith connected very well to send it caressing through the covers for four
full again and it's driven down to long-off this time
back of length outside off, Smith stays in the crease to defend it
on length towards the off stump, Smith defends off the back foot
fuller outside off, driven straight to cover off the front foot
full on the pads and Smith is not going to let that opportunity go. He flicks it off his pads, off the back foot through midwicket for four
back of length on middle with the angle, he stays back to defend
fuller and angling away further and Smith drives it past point in the gap. Afridi is on the chase and dives just in time to cut it off and he saves a run
tossed up outside off, pushed back to the bowler
comes down, he pitches it short, it turns, but Smith gets enough to push it with an edge to point
fuller now outside off, he stays in to defend again
appeal for lbw but it was drifting in and hit him in front of leg, was going down further

edged and that's been taken by the keeper, good catch! It was short of length outside off, Smith went back to cut but it didn't turn and held its line instead. He got an outside edge and it was taken very close to the off stump by Sarfraz
flighted on length outside off, Bailey waits for it and pushes to point after the turn
full and outside off, Warner doesn't move much but drives it delicately with good timing between point and cover point for two
angled in towards the pads, he flicks it to fine leg for one
on length on middle, Bailey leans a bit and pushes towards midwicket
length delivery well outside off with the angle, left alone
beats him! Touch shorter just outside off with the angle, Bailey stayed where he was to push and missed it
fuller just outside off, Bailey gets bat and pushes it to point
full on middle, Warner goes down on a knee and slog-sweeps it through midwicket in the air for a four. He's not going to buckle under pressure here
pitches outside leg and goes down further for a wide
closer to leg, Warner went back to tuck it fine but it spun sharply and went past the keeper and leg slip as Warner let it go for five wides
on length outside off, he goes back to work it on leg and it drops well short of leg slip
swept again! It wasn't full on off stump, he got a top edge but got enough to get four towards the fine leg four four
goes shorter and flatter and Warner stays back to work it on leg for one
he comes down the track and pushes it down to long-off for one
flighted on length on middle, Warner sweeps again but there's a fielder at deep fine leg. Fawad run across to dive to his left but the ball goes through him
length ball on the off stump, he stays back to defend it
fuller and wider outside off, he lets it go easily
touch shorter on off, Bailey defends off the back foot
shorter and wider outside off, he cuts but misses. Replays suggest there was a noise when the ball crossed the bat as there was a stifled appeal from Pakistan
length ball outside off, left alone easily
full and wide and Bailey leans forward to drive it between cover point and point in the gap for four
starts from length outside off, Warner tries a switch sweep but can't connect
tries the conventional sweep now and gets one down to fine leg for two
shorter one outside off, slap-swept to deep midwicket for one
flighted and full on off, drives it down to long-off for one
turning in from outside off, Warner goes back and defends
quicker and fuller towards off stump, pushed down to mid-on
full on off, Bailey defends it back
flatter down the leg side, Bailey sweeps but can't connect properly
on length on middle and leg, Bailey blocks it back
leans forward to defend the length ball on off stump
touch shorter on off and middle, Bailey goes back and taps it to midwicket
similar length on leg stump, turned towards short fine leg for one and he avoids the maiden
loud appeal for lbw, it's turned down! It was on length on the middle stump but it was drifting down, and probably going down leg from where it hit Bailey
length ball on off stump, Bailey leans forward and defends
full and flighted on off, he blocks it back
on length again, Bailey pushes to cover after pressing forward
wide down the leg side from short of length as it didn't turn
what a beauty! It was on length right on off, decent flight, Bailey came forward to defend but the ball turned and bounced to just beat the outside edge
beaten again, was that a catch? Bailey pushed again outside off and the turn beat him again, Sarfraz didn't catch it on first attempt

that would have gone for six if Irfan was not at long-on! Warner slog-swept the flighted delivery from well outside off down to long-on. It was surely going for six, but look who's there - Irfan. He jumps and takes a good catch well over his head with his arms stretched, which means the ball was about 10 feet above the ground
on length on the off stump, pushed to cover point by Maxwell
he takes a step down and pushes the ball back to the bowler
on length outside off, Bailey lets it go
length delivery on off, soft defence towards short cover and the keeper and slip run to get the ball
bit of flight outside off, he comes down and pushes it to cover
quick and down leg for a wide
short and flat outside off, cut off the back foot to point
flighted yorker drifting towards leg, Maxwell blocks it to the leg side
slower through the air as it pitched outside off and turned away further, left alone
fuller and drifting in to leg, Maxwell blocks it back
flighted and full on off, pushed with a drive towards point where Shehzad dives but can't collect cleanly which concedes a single
on length outside off, forward defence to cover form Bailey

dropped at slip! Hasan made Maxwell drive with some flight outside off, the batsman pushed forward, got an edge and it went to Akmal's left at slip but he wasn't quick enough to react. Got a hand to it, but didn't catch it
run out chance, not quite. Maxwell pushed the ball to cover point and ran for one but was sent back and he made it in time
touch shorter on middle and that's pushed down to mid-on
bit of flight outside leg and that's launched over square leg! Went down on a knee and cleared the boundary the way he used to during the IPL
over cover this time, gets some room and smacks it with a loft for four in the gap
fuller and quicker on the middle, defended to the leg side
tosses this one up and Bailey drives it to long off
slower this time, grips the surface and turns away, Maxwell defends to off
he stays in the crease and pushes the legbreak softly towards cover
nice loop from Lala, the batsman watches the drift and defends it down the pitch
quicker one this time, the batsman pushes it to deep cover for a single
tosses it up on off, the batsman pushes it to cover
slower and loopy on off, draws the batsman forward. Maxwell pushes it softly through cover
he steps out but realises he is not to the pitch of the delivery, defends it to cover
superb delivery! Tossed up, dips in, then screams past the outside edge of the outstretched batsman
comes from wide of the crease and tosses it up, the batsman defends it down the pitch
smart bowling! This is flatter and shorter as Zulfiqar sees the batsman advance.. it turns away from the batsman and he has to defend it to off
pushed through on off stump, Maxwell punches it to deep cover off the back foot
too much air this time, the batsman takes it on the full but drives it straight to midwicket
this slips out from his hands probably.. way down the leg side.. Would have been a wide but Bailey swings and slaps it past short fine leg
tosses it up outside off, drawing the batsman forward, the batsman pushes it to point
he takes a punt and slogs across the line at this fuller delivery! Drags it from outside off and whack it goes over midwicket
here comes the googles.. spins in from outside off. Not sure the batsman spotted it but he manages to defend it to the leg side
well done by Asad at first slip! (where is Umar?) The batsman gets a thick outside edge that is running away from the slip fielder, but he dives and prevents the runs
he leaves this one alone! But that is so close to off stump.. That didn't turn at all
comes in from wide of the crease, then breaks away sharply.. Maxwell defends off the back foot
he goes deep in the crease and works against the turn to punch this one down to wide mid-on
the arm-ball now! Bailey comes forward and defends
he goes for the sweep but is not entirely in control, it flies through square leg and they take a single to the deep
fuller delivery on the stumps, Maxwell is not looking to hit big, defends it to the leg side
he goes back and punches the length delivery through cover for a single to the deep
he tries to defend this back of length delivery but gets a thick inside edge that rolls over to square leg
he stands tall at the crease and punches the back of length delivery back down the pitch
this hustles Maxwell, it's quick and raps him on the pads, but this was going down the leg side and over the stumps
he stays on the back foot and defends the length delivery to cover point

Superb delivery! excellent stuff.. This one drifts in, dips, then fizzes past the outside edge. The keeper goes up, then everyone else joins in and it's a full-fledged appeal. The umpire agrees. Bailey asks for a review immediately. I don't see much evidence to turn the decision.. but they have overturned the decision. This is going a bit against the protocol in my view..there was no evidence to turn that decision around
he eases this one to long off to pick up a single
the arm-ball this time, the batsman defends it to the leg side
this one turns away, the batsman defends it to the off side now
a wide is signalled as this one is down the leg side but Sarfraz says it flicked the pads.. he is right
slower and tossed up, he is keeping the pressure on, Maxwell can only defend
he goes deep in the crease and clips it to the leg side but cannot beat midwicket
he gets an inside edge as he hangs his bat this length delivery, it wasn't too far from the leg stump
length delivery without much room but Maxwell manages to punch it to deep cover
straight and on a tight length, not much the batsman can do with it, he defends it down the pitch
this one comes in a shade in after pitching, the batsman defends it to the leg side
he dabs this short of length delivery towards square leg for a quick single
short delivery attempted, but this is ill-directed, down the leg side
he cuts it firmly through point but it only costs a single as their is protection in the deep
he pulls out the reverse sweep and gets the ideal delivery for it too - a low full toss. That has been hit hard and it screams to the boundary at backward point
looks to hit to the top of Burj Khalifa with a cross-batted swipe, makes no connection
now he calms his nerves by leaving this one alone.. not sure if he knew it was so close to off stump
he punches this in the air through the off side, oohs and aahs as this goes towards long off
slower and flatter, the batsman defends it to backward point
angled delivery, Bailey nudges it behind square on the leg side and calls for a quick second
length delivery just outside off, Maxwell stays back and pushes it down the pitch, back to the bowler
length delivery outside off, Maxwell stays patient, defends it to off again
flatter and it spins away, the batsman has all the time to punch it to deep cover
tosses it up, the batsman drives it down to long off for a single
he goes across the line and wants to go downtown, but misses again.. this one lands on the middle stump line and spins away sharply
tossed up and full on the leg stump line, the batsman digs it out to midwicket
keeps it tight around the middle stump, the batsman leans forward and defends
much shorter this time, stops on the surface too, the batsman goes back and flat-bats it down to long on
slower and loopy on the stumps, the batsman dabs it towards point for a single
flatter and outside off, easily punched away to deep extra cover for a single
much slower this time, he gets the outside edge but it just lands short of first slip.. Asad is a happy man.. dives to his right and makes the stop
he dabs it behind square on the leg side and calls for a quick single
tosses it up, Maxwell plays the reverse sweep and picks up a couple to deep backward point
here comes the cross-batted slog and finally he makes connection with the ball, drags it from outside off and hammers it over midwicket for a boundary
slightly short but the line is good. Maxwell goes deep in the crease and works it away to deep midwicket
bowls a low full toss as he strives for the loop, Bailey misses out, drives it back to the bowler
nice teasing delivery outside off, turns away sharply, Bailey leaves it alone
draws the batsman forward with a wider line, the batsman defends it to point
Maxwell smacks it well! He stays back, spots the marginally short delivery early and he thumps it over wide long on with utter ease.. that is way over the boundary
he lunges forward and drives this loopy delivery to deep extra cover firmly
slower this time from Lala, Maxwell defends it to off
looks for the sweep but this hits the pads and rolls towards short fine leg
quicker this time, turns away, the batsman defends it to off
superb ball! This one is a touch fuller, draws the batsman forward and beats him all ends up with the sharp turn and bounce.. Bailey can only smile
loud appeal for lbw as this one raps the pads, but looks like it was just going down the leg side. Maxwell played outside the line
here comes the reverse sweep, Maxwell's go to shot and he plays it well, smokes it over backward point easily
he stands tall and punches the flatter delivery to deep cover
he takes a step down the crease but defends it down the pitch
much slower this time from Raza, the batsman defends it to off
he waits on the back foot and pushes it straight to cover

fuller and comes with some space, the batsman slices it to deep point to pick up a couple to bring up his half-century - must be one of his slowest but this is what Australia need. Makes most of that early drop
back of length delivery on off, the batsman punches it to midwicket
this one is slightly slower, Maxwell has to wait an extra second, he punches this one to mid on
this one slides past the face of the bat! It was an angled delivery and Maxwell was trying to run it down to third man, but it was too close
stays back to a length delivery and dabs it towards cover, calls for a quick single
short of length and wide outside off, Bailey looks to cut it but this just bounces a touch extra, like it always does for Irfan, past the outside edge again
he is getting better now! Just spots the length disturbances so early.. this is only marginally short, he goes back and whacks it easily over midwicket
and now the reverse sweep! He makes no attempt to keep it down, thumps it over backward point
now he comes forward and chips it towards long-off with the straightest of bats
flatter and quicker on the stumps, Bailey is in no hurry, he defends

direct hit! Bailey is in trouble here. Bailey looked to hit that loopy delivery across the line, but Shehzad dives to his right at midwicket and makes a smart stop.. Bailey had taken off though.. he has to make an about turn.. and Shehzad has a direct hit too.. You see Bailey flat on his belly in the replay, fully stretched trying to make it back.. but he is gone.. Marginally short of crease. That would do. That is what Pakistan needed
a tossed up ball driven to long off for a single
moves across to a good length legbreak and turns it square on leg off middle
opens the face as he comes forward and runs it to point
wanted to dab it fine but pulled out as he saw it bouncing outside off
forward to push a legbreak to covers
slanted in full down the pads and turned to deep square leg
flat legbreak on a length, slapped to extra cover
he chips it over extra cover but not sure how he got there! It was almost in the blockhole in the middle stump line, more of a leading edge there
slower delivery on the stumps, the batsman comes forward defends
he comes down the track and murders it over midwicket, lots of bottom hand in that shot.. one bounce and four
another cross-batted sweep, but he is beaten in the flight a touch.. manages to drag it to deep backward square leg
he edges this one and for the third time, it lands short of first slip.. Asad is sharp there but hasn't got a real chance
quicker delivery on the stumps, the batsman defends it down the pitch
this one down the leg side but Maxwell reverse sweep it from there and drags it to deep cover.. Some guy this
bowls the quicker one on off, the batsman defends it down the pitch
loopy on the off stump, the batsman pushes it straight to cover
he looks to flight the ball but loses direction, it's down the leg side and it's swept to deep backward square leg
the leg stump line again, Maxwell sweeps but misses, gets hit on the waist and runs along for a leg bye
stretches out and looks to drive this wide delivery through cover, ambitious shot to say the least.. misses it completely
flatter outside off, the batsman chops it away to deep point
tossed up outside off, the batsman checks his drive and pushes it to cover
aerial shot, but this lands safely, much before reaching long off
flatter on off, the batsman stays back and punches it down to long on
he waits on the back foot and works it against the turn to midwicket
much slower and with a lot of flight, the batsman lunges forward and defends
short of length on the stumps, Maxwell looks to hammer it over the leg side but doesn't get the timing, pushes it to mid-on
slips the quicker one outside off, he beats the bat as Maxwell makes not connection with the cut shot
fires it full on off, Maxwell digs it out to mid-off and calls for a quicks single. Could have been tight, but Misbah is a little slow to the ball
another full delivery, Faulkner jams his bat at that and pushes it to extra cover
he is surprised a touch.. Wanted to duck under this short of length delivery, but is too late.. Finally has to fend it off to the off side
another one rearing up towards the chest, this time he defends it with a bit more intent, dabs it to point
this was in Maxwell's zone! He was aiming to send it over deep square leg but somehow misses..gets hit on the pads
now steps out of the crease and whips it over midwicket with utter ease.. there is no one back there.. it rolls away

top edge! This could be the end.. it is the end! Maxwell goes for another slog sweep but this just a touch shorter for the shot.. it stopped on the pitch too! It swirls in the night sky .. but Asad runs all the way from first slip to short fine leg to take a smart catch..
tossed up and slower, the batsman comes forward and pushes it calmly to long off
fuller and flighted on the stumps, Haddin defends it to the leg side
he comes forward and defends this flighted delivery solidly
he charges down the pitch and makes room but Irfan's bounce is too much for him.. It skims over the top edge of the bat
loud shout for caught behind! This is a sharp bouncer, this is a menacing bouncer.. The batsman pulls but misses.. it wasn't too far from the bat.
he makes room and this time makes the connection! Crashes this length delivery through cover..  there is no one in the deep and it rolls to the boundary
fired on the blockhole, the batsman digs it out down the pitch
he fends this short delivery to backward square leg and calls for a quick single
tossed up delivery on off, the batsman comes forward to defend, pushes it down the pitch
slower and shorter, the batsman punches it to deep extra cover easily
honing on the middle stump, the batsman is calm, defends it down the pitch
lobbed up in the air, Faulkner comes forward and drives it to long off
slower and loopy on off, Haddin is in no hurry, defends it off the back foot
slightly drifting towards the pads, Haddin dabs it towards midwicket and opens his account
he looks to cut this away but chops it straight to backward point
smartly done! He waits an extra second to allow the ball to turn, then opens the face of the bat to cut it past the lone slip fielder
even better! he waits on the back foot and punches the shorter delivery easily through extra cover
there is no calmness about this one! Sees this is full and he slogs it over long on for a huge hit.. Clean swing there
now goes back to his back-foot routine, cuts the flatter delivery to deep cover
this spins away but Faulkner pushes it easily to deep cover for a single
gets some turn from a length, but there is no pace on the delivery, the batsman defends it
gets some legbreak going from the leg stump line but it's easily dabbed to midwicket for an easy single
superb delivery, but it's all too late! This one drifts in, then breaks away past the outside edge
it stays a touch low on off, but easily defended to the off
full and flighted, it's pushed back to the bowler
he dabs it to cover with soft hands and calls over for a quick single
back of length on off stump, Haddin shuffles across and defends that solidly to the off side
bowls the fuller length this time but Haddin stays rooted to the crease, gets an outside edge as he pokes at it, however, it lands short of slip yet again
punches it firmly on the up and that travels to mid-off in quick time.. some timing there.. but straight to the fielder
looks for the yorker but it's a low full toss, all Haddin can do is punch it back to the bowler, who grabs it with his left hand and fires a throw back at the batsman
he looks to pull the back of length delivery but gets hurried by the pace, gets a bit of bottom edge to fine leg
this shoots up from  a short of length, Faulkner sees it early and drops his wrists to let it go through
tossed up delivery on the stump, the batsman takes it on the full and eases it to long on
he waits on the back foot and punches it down the pitch, back to the bowler
allows the ball to turn, then pushes it to backward point
stands tall and punches it to deep extra cover.. the fielder is a touch slow so they come back for the second
tossed up on off, the batsman dabs it to the gap at cover and picks up another single
full and flighted, driven straight to cover
they want to finish this fast! He takes this attempted yorker on the full, clears his front leg and hammers it through extra cover
game over! Faulkner moves to the leg side and slaps the length delivery over mid-off to complete the series win
